 Vehicle pollution.  According to the company, the machine will remove carbon deposits from all engine types, restore engine performances and fuel consumption, reduce exhaust fumes and prevents wear and tear of expensive engine parts. The Country Director, Sope Babaniji, said the essence of the innovation was to help car owners and motorists cut unnecessary spending due to bad fuel and other issues that arise from carbon build up in engines. He said the device is a unique-hydrogen powered decarbonizing machine with advanced technology developed over several years, which has cleaning capacity to flush out 75% of the carbon deposits that prevent cars from running smoothly. Babaniji said the device is available for purchase by automobile technicians, fleet mangers, and motor parts dealers seeking to improve their expertise.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .